{
  "stem": "17426.3",
  "chunk_idx": 2,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 12.0,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And then we traded our clothing.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "We traded our bedding, and we traded everything that we had, and finally we had nothing to trade for.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And the prices was staggering.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "Every day, a bread was going up enormously, and so that finally it wasn't any use to trade because you got really nothing for what you had.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Yes.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "The rationing system was very inefficient and very haphazard.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Whatever they had, they give it to the Judenrat.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And the Judenrat will deliver it to the ghetto, and then the ghetto, it would be distributed to each person.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "It would be announced that we come to pick up bread, and then we would get 300 to 400 grams of bread.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "Then we would get, well, some potatoes and some-- often some flour and some margarine and some jam and some accidental things.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Excuse me.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Well, [SIGHS] it was a very difficult role for the Judenrat.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "I know that the Judenrat is being remembered as one of the arms of the German Reich and fulfilling the Germans Reich's desire to destroy the Jews.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "But in a sense, one had to say that they had no choice.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "They were in a untenable position.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "They were put in a position that no person ever should be put in, where they had to squeeze-- literally squeeze-- the life out of every Jew in their own community and sometime deliver them to destruction, knowing that they're going to be destroyed.",
      "word_count": 44
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And so in 1941, early in May, the Judenrat got the order from Mr.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "Schweickert to deliver every Jewish male between the age of 16 and 60 for deportation to a labor camp, with the exception of one male that could remain with each family.",
      "word_count": 31
    }
  ],
